oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Portrait photograph of William Josiah Sanders, Jr.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This small rectangular photograph of William Josiah Sanders, Jr. has had the corners of the image clipped. The subject is dressed in a coat and vest with bowtie. Sanders was born Oct. 29, 1893 and died April 11, 1961. Sanders served in the World War, 1914-1918. See his journalGWnash073.
